title: For Sale:  Definitely not a scammer
postcontent:
Hi all. I had a bad deal with an individual. I'm not here to put his name on blast because I can see why he would be upset. I agreed to trade my AR Pistol for a DD Upper. He lives outside of Jackson, and we met halfway. It was a very sketchy abandonded truck stop, had I seen the location before, I never would have went there. I drove there in my gfs car with her in it because my car's 5th gear is out. It was a very sketchy, "The Hills have Eyes/ Texas Chainsaw Massacre" looking place and I felt uncomfortable the whole time. I traded him a firearm that I bought new, and assumed worked. He called me the next day and left a very angry voicemal (because I was at work and didn't answer right away) and told me it would not chamber. I IMMEDIATELY called him back to address the issue. He told me he took it apart, cleaned it, messed with it, took a "copper brush" to it and it would not chamber. I had no idea it would not chamber. I never tried to fire or chamber it. I don't shoot every gun I own. But alas, I told him I am a man of my word and had no issue giving him his item back, even swap. My only request was he come to my work, which is a LICENSED FFL, and have my LICENSED Gunsmith look at it to make sure it wasn't altered or parts switched out. I even offered to pay for his gas. He responded very immaturely (as presented in the photos).I've traded with probably half of you guys on here, I work some of the gun shows, and most of you know where I work. You guys know me. I've yet to have a bad transaction until now. I work for an FFL with a Gunsmith. I have ZERO reason to trade off non working firearms. I'd just have my gunsmith fix it, or send it off to the manufacturer. I was just uncomfortable meeting a man who left me a very angry message, in an abandonded delapidated truck stop, in my gfs car with her 5'3" 110lbs blonde ass sitting in the seat while I meet an irrationally pissed up guy about a gun trade. I don't want to end up on an episode of the first 48. Plus, I had no idea what he might have done with it. I don't know wtf a "copper brush" is that he took to my pistol, he states he took it apart and messed with it. I don't know what he did to it. His firearm knowledge seemed very lacking as well, as he believed 7.5" AR uppers had to be pinned and welded, so I can't seem to say I trust he may not have messed my firearm up, then caused a scene trying to get his back.I'm not meeting a guy to get a gun back he might of broken or altered and I'm liable to take the gun back due to the shady situation and location.Bottom line, I called him back, emailed, gave an option, and even offered to cover his gas and he still refuses. I'm still 100% willing to switch back, so Gerald, let me know. Thanks all!I'll also be attaching screenshots of his responses so you guys can decide for yourselves. If you'll notice, I didn't put the guys info, number, or email on it, because I'm not about putting someone on blast. I would be upset if I were in his shoes too, I understand. But I did do more than enough to try to make it right, just short of meeting him at the shooting local of House of 1,000 Corpes.EDIT 2/28/18:He reposted haha! Thanks for all the emails laughing at this dude and support. I had a guy I was trading with the last time "sketchy guy" posted this nonsense send me a text and tell me he was "uneasy" with trading with me after reading the post. I told him I totally understood, but offered to tell my side of the story as well. I sent him the screenshots and he told me he was fine with dealing with me after seeing the other guys response. Traded my Weatherby Vanguard for an FNS-9. Good trade. Awesome dude, he came in the shop and we talked for a bit. 
The dude is twice my age and acting like he's half of it. I have his name, number, address, wifes number and all sorts of other info that I could blast out if I was a lesser man, but I'm not. Point is, I've got no problem trading with any of you, and if any of you wonderful folks on Armslist wish to deal at an FFL, doesn't even have to be the one I work at, I'd be more than willing to do so! I take my reputation seriously! I've gotten about 7 or 8 responses from this post, and all but one have been positive. I appreciate the support guys. This post has made me a few new friends on here, so I guess not all is bad!Thanks and take care folks!
